item.title: Jdk
item.dc:creator: @Le_Jitt Le Jitt
item.description:
@Le_Jitt wrote:

Ok Right Click And Click Edit.

Then Press Ctrl F And Type Jdk.

Change The Version Of JDK To The One That’s In Your Program Files So E.G.

"C:/Program Files/Java/[b][u]Jdk1.6.0_03/Bin[/u][/b]

Change The Jdk Version To The One That You Have So If You Have Jdk 6 Update 4 Change To .0_04 Etc.

Note
Change All Of The Jdk Versions To Yours So That It Will DEFFINATLY Find It.

Any More Help Just Ask.

Hope This Helps.
